Uchumi of Kenya Falls for 5th Day on Bet Inflation to Curb Spend

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-06-29T12:23:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-29/uchumi-of-kenya-falls-for-5th-day-on-bet-inflation-to-curb-spend.html
Uchumi Supermarkets Ltd.,  Kenya ’s 
only publicly traded retailer, fell for a fifth day on bets
inflation, which accelerated for an eighth straight month in
East Africa’s biggest economy, will hurt retail sales .  The shares fell 45 cents, or 3.9 percent, to 11.05
shillings by the 3 p.m. close in the capital, Nairobi, its
longest streak of losses since the company resumed trading on
May 31 after a five-year suspension due to bankruptcy.  The annual inflation rate increased to 14.5 percent in June
from 13 percent in May, the Kenya National Bureau of Statistics
said in an e-mailed statement today.  “Fundamentally inflation has a very substantial negative
effect on the economy,” George Bodo, an equity strategist at
Nairobi-based Apex Africa Ltd., a brokerage, said in a phone
interview today. “Our economy is partly driven by robust
domestic consumption through retail sales.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
